3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper may also touch on issues related to the societal impact of security protocols and encryption communication.
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may discuss information theory concepts related to encryption and authentication protocols.
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may also discuss software engineering aspects of implementing the proposed security protocol.
